It could be argued that for FLOAT DECIMAL it is a precision 
specification in decimal digits.  Still, on a machine with both binary 
and decimal floating point hardware, I would expect it to use the 
decimal hardware.

FLOAT DECIMAL can be implemented using binary arithmetic, but it takes 
lots of multiply and divide by powers of ten for scaled values.
(There is at least one IBM compiler that does it.)

