Stratus VOS PL/I is basically ANSI Subset G PL/I (X3.74-1981).  We have a
few extra features from the full language and a few proprietary extensions,
but for the most part, it stays close to the Subset G language. That's not
surprising since the author of Subset G was the author of the front-end of
the Stratus PL/I compiler (Bob Freiburghouse).

Multics PL/I was pretty close to full ANSI PL/I.  (X3.53-1976)  Bob
eventually sold a version of his TSI PL/I compiler that handled ANSI PL/I as
well.

The Multics PL/I compiler and the TSI PL/I compilers are totally separate
implementations.  About all you can say is that some of the same people
worked on both of them, including me.

