The AS/400 PL/I compiler has been a RPQ since V3R6 of the operating system
introduced well five years ago as licensed program 5799-FPJ

Since then despite IBM's assurances that it would be removed in a future
version of OS/400, the RPQ has been refreshed twice

In V4R2, the licensed program is called 5799-GCG
For V5R1, just announced, the RPQ P10144. The product number will be
5799-GKK.

For the casually interested, AS/400's version of the PL/I compiler only
implements subset G with some very minor OS/400 specific enhancements.

Subset G is *VERY* limited and barely qualifies to be titled PL/I. But even
so, the language is far superior to the other OS/400 languages (RPGIII,
RPG/400, RPG IV, Cobol, C)







