 From ANSI X3.74-1987 Programming Language - PL/I General-Purpose Subset:

     Appendix A.8  Built-in Functions and Pseudo-variables
     ...
     3.  ONSOURCE pseudo-variable

         This pseudo-variable allows a copy of the character-string
         source value that caused a CONVERSION condition to be modified
         so that the conversion may be re-tried.


The PL/I ANSI standard is a little complicated; I only have a PDF
version at home and I'm much more comfortable with the hardcopy version.
  Nevertheless, the quotation above seems to indicate an assignment to
the ONSOURCE pseudo-variable is an assignment to a copy of the field
causing the CONVERSION condition rather than an assignment to the
original field itself.

Of course there's always the question of whether any specific compiler
is standard-conforming.


