The last documentation I have for Liant's PL/I (dated 1990) claims
compatibility with the general purpose subset, ANSI X3.74-1981 plus
some extensions.  The care they took to comply with that ANSI standard
should make it easy to port any programs using only general purpose
subset features.

However, Shmuel is correct: full PL/I has additional features and
IBM PL/I probably has features not included in the full ANSI PL/I
standard.  The general purpose subset has a fairly robust set of
features but some programmers seem to take pride in using every
obscure feature they can discover so the best bet is to communicate
with Liant directly.


