I am considering working again on my PL/I compiler for NT.

I would like some answers first however:

Question 1 versions:

There are three printed standards:

ANSI X3.53-1976 (Large and similar to IBM/Full PL/I)

ANSI X3.74-1981 (Small and quite restrictive)

ANSI X3.74-1987 (Large and better than 1981, but not as large as 1976)

So called 'IBM/Full PL/I' (Large and to my knowledge no language
definition exists, so its 'closed' and only IBM know its formal
definition)

Which of these are people interested in ?

Question 2 features

Would you be happy with just a compiler, and use your own editor, and
linker etc ?

Or do you want a complete featured IDE (like microsofts devstudio) ?

Question 3 Platform

What platform is of most interest 

DOS ?
Win16 ?
Win95 ?
WinNT ?
Linux ?
Other ?

Please email me with your views on these questions, I may restart the
project if I get the right interest, and its price would be a lot less
than any competing compiler.

I would like to interface PL/I with the Win32 API to allows
sophisticated products to be developed.

Thanks

Hugh






