>>Why do I allow nesting ?

>>Well it allows you to comment out large chunks of code and
>>comments in one hit:

>But PL/I (IBM PL/I and Burroughs PL/I at least)
>has an extremely powerful (and elaborate) preprocessor,
>which renders an extra mechanism as useful as tits on a bull.

>If you are going to add things to PL/I that are not in the
