IBM's PL/I compilers dont implement an ANSI standard.

Preprocessing isnt included in ANSI.

The X3.74-1987 standard is the latest standard.

Like I said nesting comments allows arbitrary blocks of commented code
to be commented out. This is so useful (especially for testing the
compiler) that I include it. Its an optional extension, such things
are common in this business.








