"James R. Cordy" <cordy@legasys.on.ca> wrote:

>I am interested in obtaining a public domain online grammar
>for PL/I, or a large (say, PL/C-sized) subset of it.  
>If anyone knows of the whereabouts of such a beast, please let me know.

>Thanks
>Jim Cordy

>PS I am not interested in commercial products.

Do you want the grammar in order to build a parser ?
Do you want the grammar in some special format ?
The grammar for PL/I is rather complex, the one I used
is the ANSI X3.74-1987 document (450 pages).

Be warned the document is abstruse.

For example it describes PL/I in terms of TWO syntaxes
a 'concrete' syntax and an 'abstract' syntax. 

I used this document to help me write a recursive-descent
parser in 'C' for my windows NT PL/I compiler, if you want to see the
results check out

ftp.winsite.com

in

ftp/pub/pc/winnt/miscutil

called

pli-32.zip

Let me know if you track down a 'grammar', id be interested
in what you dig up.

Regards, Hugo.





