I have almost fully implemented the parser for my port of my old DOS
PL/I compiler to NT.

I now have a full Win32 PL/I executable. It doesnt yet produce code,
but It wont be too hard to modify the 16 80286 codegen to 32 bit 486,
586 etc.

In the meantime, I would like to get hold of 'real' PL/I source code
that I can use to stress the parser to its limits.

The parser in the latest version supports (in addition to the DOS
version):

All stream and record IO statements and options.
All looping constructs
All forms of the INITIAL option on declares.

The parser implements ANSI X3.74-1987 this does NOT refer in any way
to preprocessing (as used by IBM M/F) except %include.

So if anybody has any source code that I can have, please Email it to
me so that I can stress the parser.

There is a ZIP file that contains a full test version including sample
