Get a copy of ANSI X3.53-1976 (ANSI Standard PL/I), or X3.74-1987 (General 
Purpose Subset PL/I). They have enough BNF for PL/I to make your head swim. Of 
course, it is ANSI PL/I, not IBM PL/I, but you should be able to understand it 
well enough to improve it.  See http://www.ansi.org/.

